      What is the difference between a finishing spray and a hairspray?
      An AI Overview is not available for this searchCan't generate an AI overview right now. Try again later.
      AI Overview
      The main difference is purpose: finishing sprays provide a flexible, touchable hold and add shine, while hairsprays offer strong, long-lasting hold to lock a style in place, but can sometimes lead to stiffness. Finishing sprays are excellent for enhancing natural movement, reducing frizz, and setting delicate updos, whereas traditional hairspray is better for securing intricate styles, setting curls, and providing maximum longevity for more structured looks.
       
      Finishing Spray
      • Purpose:
        Adds shine, reduces frizz and flyaways, and provides a lightweight, flexible hold. 
      • Hold:
        Offers a light to medium hold, keeping hair bouncy and touchable without stiffness or residue. 
      • Finish:
        Delivers brilliant shine, humidity resistance, and a sleek, smooth look. 
      • Best For:
        Setting finished styles, enhancing shine on sleek looks, adding volume, and taming flyaways on delicate updos. 
      Hairspray
      • Purpose:
        To lock hair into place, provide a strong hold, and ensure a style lasts. 
      • Hold:
        Can range from flexible to strong hold, creating a protective coating of polymers that bond hair fibers together. 
      • Finish:
        Depending on the product, it can offer volume, but some formulas can leave hair feeling stiff or sticky. 
      • Best For:
        Securing intricate updos, defining curls, and prolonging the life of any hairstyle needing extra control. 
      Key Differences
      • Hold vs. Shine:
        Hairspray prioritizes hold and locking styles, while finishing spray focuses on shine, flexibility, and a softer finish. 
      • Flexibility:
        Finishing sprays are designed for a more natural feel, allowing for movement and touchable hair, whereas strong-hold hairsprays can make hair feel stiffer. 
      • Usage:
        Finishing spray is the final touch to add gloss and control, whereas hairspray is a versatile styling product used at various stages, including as a finisher, to keep hair in place.
